					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You actually have the answer in your own comments:<br /><div class="quotetitle">DRW wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">	; Pointer + 0<br />	; is always 0.<br /></div><br /><br />The writes go<br />Y=0, $0=0, $1=0 thus 0→$0<br />Y=1, $0=0, $1=0 thus 0→$1<br /><br />And after that, nothing writes to the pointer memory again.<br /><br />Since the pointer has to be stored in zero page, and you're initializing RAM with 0, it won't miss anything.</div>

