				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yes in this case you will need X and Pointer+1 to be equal otherwise you will always write $0800 bytes, and since the NES repeats RAM again after $0800 you end up writing to $0000 again.<br /><br />so for example $0200 + $0700 = $0900 which is the same as $0100 which will explain why you don't see any X's in the case where you try to only clear part of it.</div>

