						<div class="postbody">I was lucky that it works in my game &quot;City Trouble&quot; simply because the reset-persitent area is only 13 bytes big and it isn't positioned in a location where the low byte overflows and the high byte gets incremented. So, Pointer + 1 remains the same before and after that check anyway.<br />But programming-wise it's of course a bug and I'll correct it for the next game.</div>

					
