				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">mikejmoffitt wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Why such a complicated RAM-clearing routine?<br /><br />Adapted from the wiki:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp;ldx #0<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;txa $0<br /><br />@clrmem_top:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta $000, x<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta $100, x<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;; Reserving $200 for OAM display list, sta $200, x if you want<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta $300, x<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta $400, x<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta $500, x<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta $600, x<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta $700, x<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;inx<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;bne @clrmem_top<br /></div></div><br />His version is not very complicated, in fact it's pretty much standard, and note the fact that while your version is faster, his version is more compact: your algorithm takes 27 bytes, his takes 22 bytes, and could take only 20 bytes if we didn't care of the pointer value at the end. For some code initializing things, ran once at the beginning, speed is not important, but size is.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />((λ (x) (x x)) (λ (x) (x x)))</div>
